  "prompt": "Why does Audible.com take away all my credits when my membership expires? Didn't I pay for those credits last year?",
  "response": "When you purchase an Audible membership, you receive a certain number of credits each month (or all at once, depending on your plan) as part of that membership. These credits are essentially a benefit of being an active member, and their use is tied to the terms of your subscription.\n\nHere\u2019s why Audible takes away unused credits when your membership expires:\n\n1. **Credits Are Part of the Membership**: Credits are not standalone purchases but rather a perk of your Audible subscription. They are intended to be used while you are an active member. If your membership lapses, you lose access to these credits because they are no longer part of your active subscription benefits.\n\n2. **Expiration Policy**: Audible's terms of service clearly state that unused credits expire when your membership ends. This policy is in place to encourage active use of the service and to prevent the accumulation of unused credits over time.\n\n3. **Credits Are Not Purchased Individually**: While you may feel like you \"paid for\" the credits, they are not individually purchased. Instead, they are part of the overall package of your membership. If you cancel your membership, the entire package, including unused credits, is no longer valid.\n\n### What Can You Do to Prevent Losing Credits?\n- **Use Your Credits Before Canceling**: If you plan to cancel your membership, make sure to use all your credits to purchase audiobooks before the cancellation takes effect. These audiobooks will remain in your library even after your membership ends.\n- **Pause Your Membership**: Audible sometimes offers the option to pause your membership for a few months instead of canceling it. This can allow you to retain your credits while taking a break from paying for the subscription.\n- **Check for Promotions**: Occasionally, Audible offers promotions where you can roll over unused credits or extend their expiration. Check with customer service to see if any such offers are available.\n\nIf you have questions or concerns about your credits, it\u2019s always a good idea to contact Audible customer service for clarification or assistance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
